parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel system components, such as the fuel check valve, fuel petcock, and lower rocker cover gasket, can cause issues with fuel flow, leading to engine stalling, poor performance, and potentially leaving the rider stranded.
The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal travels to the floor
brake pedal has a soft or mushy feel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel system components, such as the fuel cock or fuel gauge, can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, fuel leaks, or engine stalling, which can cause accidents, leave the driver stranded, or result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is not functioning
the fuel level reading is inaccurate
the fuel pump is noisy or malfunctioning.
